 Neuhaus, Christian Marclay, and many others, Sonic Flux contributes to the development of a materialist metaphysics and poses a challenge to the prevailing positions in cultural theory, proposing a realist and materialist aesthetics able to account not only for sonic art but for artistic production in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aMetaphysics. 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 0aSound (Philosophy) 0aSound (Philosophy). 0aSound installations (Art) 0aSound installations (Art). 0aSoundscapes (Music)xHistory and criticism. 0aSoundscapes (Music)xPhilosophy and aesthetics. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aaesthetics.  amaterialism.  ametaphysics.  anoise.  aontology.  asonic flux.  asound art.  atemporality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226543208423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226543208/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles